- `Stress verdict`: survive / degrade / split / exit / reject
- `Triggers`: pre-committed thresholds
- `Child verdict`: home / staging base / harvest-and-exit
- `Next 5 years`: rehearsals and irreversible moves only

Bottom line: v3 now has the right spine. The final improvement is not another dimension; it is forcing the framework to make harder, simpler outputs about execution, extraction, and whether a place is actually a home or just a temporary platform.

